**Steps to reproduce**

1. Index documents ranging from some time before `now` to some time after `now`. You can use the python script found [here](https://gist.github.com/dimitris-athanasiou/c7cc510365620923989944460332dd98)

2. Put job:


```
PUT _ml/anomaly_detectors/test_job
{
	"analysis_config": {
		"bucket_span": "1m",
		"summary_count_field_name": "doc_count",
		"detectors": [
			{"function": "count"}
		]
	},
	"model_plot_config": {"enabled": "true"},
	"data_description": {
		"time_field": "time"
	}
}
```

3. Open job:

```
POST _ml/anomaly_detectors/test_job/_open
```

4. Put datafeed:

```
PUT _ml/datafeeds/test_datafeed
{
	"indices": "rt",
	"job_id": "test_job",
	"query_delay": "20s",
	"aggs": {
    	"buckets": {
	    	"date_histogram": {
	        "field": "time",
	        "interval": "1m",
	        "time_zone": "UTC"
    	},
        "aggs": {
            "time": {
                "max": {
        	    "field": "time"
        	}
            }
        }
    }
  }
}
```

5. Start datafeed

```
POST _ml/datafeeds/test_datafeed/_start
```

6. Wait until a few minutes pass so that  the datafeed triggers a few real-time searches

**Observed Behaviour**

Notice that there will be an empty bucket right after the lookback ended.

